  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Delayed discharge in geriatric units is a health and economic issue. There is no algorithm to&#xD;
      automatically measure the appropriateness of admissions or hospital days. 30% of the days of&#xD;
      hospitalization in acute geriatric units (AGU) are not appropriate. Waiting for a transfer to&#xD;
      a follow-up care and rehabilitation unit (SSR) is the main risk factor for inappropriate&#xD;
      days. The purpose of this project is to develop an algorithm using natural language&#xD;
      processing to predict the appropriateness of an admission to UGA, or a day at UGA.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
